WorkItem.Description:
The type of 'val' is inferred to be Cell in the example, even though it should be Ship.  This causes a compile error.

```typescript
class Cell {
    contents: any;
}

class Ship {
    isSunk: bool;
}

class Board {
    ships: Ship[];

    private allSunk() {
        return this.ships.every(function (val) { return val.isSunk; });
    }
}
```
